executionArgs.additionalInstruction:
CRITICAL API RESPONSE SHAPES — follow EXACTLY:

POST /v1/chats response is NESTED:
  {"chat": {"id": "uuid", "title": "...", ...}}
  chat_id = response.json()['chat']['id']
  DO NOT USE response.json()['chat_id'] — THAT KEY DOES NOT EXIST

GET /v1/chats: {"items": [{"id": "...", ...}, ...]}
GET /v1/chats/{chat_id}: {"chat": {"id": "...", ...}}
GET /v1/chats/{chat_id}/shorts: {"chat_id": "...", "items": [...]}
POST /v1/chats/{chat_id}/engagement body requires item_id, viewer_id, session_id (strings). Response: {"engagement": {"id": "..."}}
GET /v1/chats/{chat_id}/recommendations: {"chat_id": "...", "has_enough_data": bool, "reels_tracked": int, ...}

chat_id path params must be valid UUIDs. Non-UUID returns 422, non-existent returns 404.
Server running at http://localhost:8000.
